g on creating an elegant and responsive display for governance alerts, utilizing clear visual cues for urgency. I am using colors for alerts, making sure to track acknowledgements.\n\n\n**Refining Dynamic Displays**\n\nI'm now adding acknowledgements and governance states. I've designed dynamic UI updates based on \"Ack\" button interactions, logging these actions in the CLI. I am also implementing verification and logging, which will update the display and show any remediation.\n\n\n**Refining Ticket Handling**\n\nI'm now refining ticket handling and dynamic state updates. I'm focusing on the \"Ack\" button to trigger UI changes and log acknowledgements in the CLI. The goal is a visually clear notification of acknowledged states and verified remediation logs, using custom colors. This is the last feature to be implemented.\n\n\n**Finalizing Visual Enhancements**\n\nI'm now implementing the financial ledger with invoice summaries, including invoice numbers, categories, and formatted amounts. I've designed the visual display for invoices, including the invoice number, description and amounts, and made sure all the data displays as expected. I'm focusing on making everything appear on the screen!\n\n\n**Finalizing Document Display**\n\nI'm now implementing the cryptographic document display with SHA-256 hashes, ensuring the \"CRYPTOGRAPHIC DOCUMENT VAULT\" displays a list of recent compliance documents with concise titles and truncated hashes. The display has a clear visual hierarchy and terminal style.\n\n\n**Finalizing Data Integration**\n\nI'm now integrating the data, and completing the dashboard implementation! The Financial Ledger and Cryptographic Document Vault are fully populated and rendering data correctly, with truncated hashes for documents and formatted invoice amounts. The lower strip is complete and fully integrated into the design. Everything looks great!\n\n\n**Verifying Key Integrations**\n\nI'm now focusing on critical imports and state management 